# UI rules

The screen contracts are in `@docs/PR_Pulse_UX_Spec.md`. Build to them.

## Design charter (standing principle)
Act as a senior UI designer: **premium, restrained, easy-to-use** for daily power-users (account managers).
- **Calm light palette** — ONE accent (`brand`) used sparingly; color is punctuation, not decoration.
- **Typography** — two weights only: regular (400) and medium (500); never heavier. Clear hierarchy via size and color, not boldness.
- **Density over sprawl** — disciplined spacing, no large empty padding; subtle `border-line/80` dividers; radii 8–12px (`rounded-md` / `rounded-lg`).
- **No heavy fills or raw default controls** — style every input, select, and button; never ship browser-default form chrome.
- **Reference data as chips/tiles** — compact chips or metric tiles, not form-blocks or run-on label:value strings.
- **Progressive disclosure** — never surface a control before its moment.
- **Shared tokens** — use kit components (`HealthBadge`, `MetricTile`, `Pill`, `SectionBlock`) so nothing is a one-off.
- **Campaign health** — always `HealthBadge` (dot + human label); never print raw colour names (`green`/`amber`/`red`).

## Structure
- **Build the primitive component kit first**, then compose every screen from it: `AppShell`, `DataTable`, `FilterBar`, `Drawer`, `SidePanel`, `ExpandableSection`, `StatusButton`, `QuickAction`, `Card`, `Pill`/`Tag`, `HealthBadge`, `RatingStars`, `Toast`, `EmptyState`, `Skeleton`, `InlineCardConfirm`. Do not invent per-screen form layouts.
- **No floating popups:** light/vital actions render **inline within the card or row** (contact-log choices, branch buttons, single-step confirms). Anything requiring heavier or multi-field input opens in the **side drawer** (schedule visit, log deliverable with proof, feedback, visit capture, deliverables editor, timeline, create forms). Never use centered modals or anchored popovers for user input.
- **Progressive disclosure:** no screen shows all of an entity's fields. Secondary workflows open in `Drawer`/`SidePanel`. **Drawers are one level deep**; on mobile they are full-screen sheets — never stack a second drawer.
- **Engagement Record stays compact:** main view = Contact, Campaign, Status, Interest, Owner, Last Contact, Next Follow-up, Agreed Fee, Notes. Deliverables / Feedback / Visit / Timeline are **drawers**, never inline sections.
- Records are **read-first** with an explicit Edit affordance. Buttons over typing.

## Mirror the DB guards in the UI (don't duplicate logic — reflect state)
- Disable **Collaboration Complete** until ≥1 deliverable exists and all are `Posted`; show the blocking reason.
- Selecting **Scheduled** requires visit date, ≥1 deliverable, and **collab reason**; block message names missing prerequisites. Schedule flow opens in the campaign quick-edit **drawer**; on save, `next_follow_up_date = visit_date`.
- Agreed Fee / Collaboration Type render **read-only while Completed** (lock + "Reopen to amend").
- **Overdue** is a computed badge from `v_deliverables`, never a status choice.

## Visual density (default for drawers & side panels)
- **Density, not sprawl:** tight vertical rhythm (`py-3` sections), modest padding, sections separated by a single subtle divider (`divide-line/80`), not large gaps.
- **Summaries as chips:** planned items (deliverables, tags) render as compact removable chips — never large bordered cards with nested controls.
- **Progressive disclosure:** don't surface a control until the stage needs it (e.g. agreed fee only when paid; follow-up hidden when complete/dropped).
- **Restraint:** subtle 0.5px borders, two font weights (regular + medium), muted uppercase micro-labels (`text-[10px] tracking-wider`) for section headers, brand accent used sparingly, minimal contextual helper text (no verbose always-on hints).
- **Section rhythm in drawers:** alternate plain sections with subtle filled blocks (`SectionBlock`) — **accent** tint (`bg-brand-soft/30`) for strategic anchors (e.g. collab reason), **neutral** canvas fill (`bg-canvas/70`) for grouped commercial content (e.g. deal + deliverables). Status, notes, and identity stay on white to avoid a wall of color.
- **Posting status:** deliverable Posted status is set only through the Awaiting Final Deliverables "Log deliverable" flow (requires proof) — never via a status dropdown in quick-edit drawers.

## Conventions
- Functional components, **named exports**, explicit prop types, Tailwind utility classes.
- **Optimistic UI** on status changes; reconcile on response; surface guard rejections as `Toast`.
- Every list, drawer, and widget implements **loading / empty / error** states.
- Dashboard widgets read **cached rollups + views**, not request-path aggregation.
- Do not use `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` for source-of-truth data; server is the source of truth.
